(thirdQuint)Doxorubicin HCI Liposome Injection Versus Weekly Docetaxel in Patients First Relapse Metastatic Breast Cancer.

 Upon determination of eligibility, patients will be randomly assigned to one of two treatment arms: - Liposomal Doxorubicin - Docetaxel For ever 2 patients treated, 1 will receive treatment A (Liposomal Doxorubicin) and 1 will receive treatment B (Docetaxel).

 Patients demonstrating progression on either ARM will be eligible for cross over to treatment in the other ARM, provided patient still meets the eligibility laboratory and performance status criteria.

 The study is not blinded so both the patient and the doctor will know which treatment has been assigned.

